<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-85DEC44D-9640-4D18-BCEE-113E04060E37" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-85DEC44D-9640-4D18-BCEE-113E04060E37" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">05 The function of the Y Motion System</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M149178-B54"><p class="- topic/p ">The most important functions of the Y Motion System (printhead carriage) are : 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol " id="OL_9AC93E9D324248E6AFB349F84DB26C35"><li class="- topic/li " id="LI_E17688106A044BAEB1CEE7EFAC14E17A"><p class="- topic/p ">Provide a stable assembly on which all 4 printheads and 4 dummy printheads are installed. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li " id="LI_17994B512D2A4A1ABE8F48184B9E8DE8"><p class="- topic/p ">Move the printheads across the media on the platen (print surface). 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li " id="LI_C4AECAF3780942989DCB58BC169BAA07"><p class="- topic/p ">Move the printheads to the maintenance position. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li " id="LI_69A60A628DF645C4A35ADA02F2C42ED9"><p class="- topic/p ">Move also the M&amp;C unit over the media. 
</p></li></ol><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-190748C9-A081-4C15-A5BD-5CA045F0FB76"><title class="- topic/title ">Location of the Y motion system at the maintenance position (marked in yellow)</title><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-E5075A1E-8936-4128-A175-33099D68C76C-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-E5075A1E-8936-4128-A175-33099D68C76C-low.png"/></fig><note class="- topic/note " id="M149178-NOE55" type="note"><p class="- topic/p ">All drive to the printhead carriage is stopped if the top cover is open(ed). 
</p></note></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="M149178-B56" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph ">Illustration</ph></title><fig id="M149178-F57" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">The printhead carriage with the 4 printheads and 4 dummy printheads</title><image href="GUID-EA57C621-EB74-4F59-B1C6-346D052167B0-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-EA57C621-EB74-4F59-B1C6-346D052167B0-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="M149178-B59" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Printhead carriage assembly</title><p class="- topic/p ">There are 4 printheads and 4 dummy printheads installed in the printer: 
</p><ul id="UL_F31DA4BC7ADD43F0BC2BE3AFA4296D67" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_0BA10FD81BEC4FA889F0C0A48BD8F264" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> PH1: Dummy printhead 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> PH2: Dummy printhead 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> PH3: Magenta (M) printhead 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> PH4: Yellow (Y) printhead 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> PH5: Black (K) printhead 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> PH6: Cyan (C) printhead 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> PH7: Dummy printhead 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> PH8: Dummy printhead 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">All of the printheads are installed inline in the printhead carriage. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> All printheads are installed in a fixed position. Each printhead has two positioning balls on its assembly. These positioning balls with a spring lock the printhead in a fixed position. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When you receive a new printhead you can insert it in any printhead position. The new printhead does not contain ink. After the correct installation procedure it is filled with ink. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">After installation you should not move the printhead to another position. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In the table below you will find the detailed descriptions of the other functions that belong to Y motion unit. 
</p><table id="M149178-TB60" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Document 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref id="X032751" keyref="FUNC05002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-A43E3777-E924-4979-9875-8ECD21A39B77.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>05 The process of the printhead carriage</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The drive mechanism of the printhead carriage. This includes the motors and sensors involved. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="FUNC05006" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-7E4AA1DB-2EBA-4D70-B1B4-5091B7E4B8FC.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>05 The process of the Measurement &amp; Control unit</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description of all functions of the M&amp;C unit. 
